<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="1176" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1176">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.63/13.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Agent <persName type="to">Carothers</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 18, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>After consulting Letcher about his 523, fourth instant, endeavor to
                            persuade Villa order reversal or modification decree Governor <pb facs="0839" n="723" xml:id="pg_723"/> Chihuahua requiring renewal
                            industrial and mining operations. Remind Villa that this Government for
                            good reasons warned its citizens to leave certain sections of Mexico,
                            state that United States will cooperate to secure return Americans so
                            soon after ordinary commercial facilities make it possible to transact
                            business as Constitutionalists give convincing evidences of security and
                            protection and that in meantime this Government expects that its
                            citizens will not be subjected to burdensome or oppressive measures.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>